President Reagan is to nominate JohnShad, chairman of the Securities and Exchange Commission, SEC,as ambassador to the Netherlands, the White House said today.    Shad, 63, a former executive with the Wall Street firm ofE.F. Hutton and Co., would succeed L. Paul Bremer, now theState Department's chief counter-terrorism expert.    The White House also said that Reagan will nominate careerdiplomat Sol Polansky, 60, as ambassador to Bulgaria. Polanskypreviously served in Moscow, Poland, East Germany, Austria andother posts.    The nominations are subject to Senate approval. Reuter&#3;